				<p>This looks like a nice guide &#8211; I have been having a problem trying to make a bootable usbkey to run a firmware update for Crucial mSATA SSD from the page at <a href="http://www.crucial.com/uk/help/ssd/index.aspx?source=web" rel="nofollow">http://www.crucial.com/uk/help/ssd/index.aspx?source=web</a> (select mSATA SSD from the pulldown list) &#8211; I have been trying to make a bootable key from the downloaded iso using several different methods including running unetbootin &#8211; but nothing I have tried gets booted on my machine (an Intel DQ77KB motherboard) &#8211; though a bootable Parted Magic iso made into a usbkey using unetbootin works fine!  So I presume there is something oddball about the firmware update iso &#8211; which has memdisk and a floppy image as a .img file in it.</p>
<p>I have been tearing my hair out trying to get it to work but maybe your method might lead to a usbkey that will boot on my system!</p>
<p>Thanks for any advice.</p>
